               <head>Tuḥfat al-āfāq by Qabūl Muḥammad</head>
               <msContents
                  class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh2010105563">
                  <summary>A Persian commentary on the <title key="work_411">Tuḥfat
                        al-ʿIrāqayn</title> of <persName role="ant" key="VIAF_302201975">Khāqānī
                        Shirvānī</persName> (1126-98), composed by Qabūl Muḥammad, son of Shaykh
                     Valī Muḥammad, resident of Singapore (Sinjabūr). Appears to be an
                     autograph.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1240-item1">
                     <author key="person_f8593">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Qabūl Muḥammad ibn Shaykh Valī
                           Muḥammad</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">قبول محمّد ولد شیخ ولی محمّد</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23474">Tūhfat al-āfāq</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa">تحفة الآفاق</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa">حمد وافر شارحی را که از متن یک رباعی عناصر بقلم قدرت
                        هزاران شرح نموده</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">امین بمد الف که بعد از دعا گویند یعنی اینچنین باد و
                        مستجاب گردان این دعا را.</explicit>
                     <colophon>(f. 208v) Completed on Tuesday, 15 Rabiʻ I 1214 AH (17 August 1799)
                        by the author, Qabūl Muḥammad in Lucknow as a service to <persName
                           role="pat" key="VIAF_1563695">Saʿādat ʻAlī Khān</persName> (d.1814),
                        Nawab of Oudh. </colophon>
                     <note>
                        <p>The colophon is also dated in the Faṣli, Samvat and Saka eras. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
