                  <handDesc>
                     <summary/>
                     <handNote>
                        <p>Shikastah; copied in black ink, headings and markings in red.
                           Copyist is <persName role="scr">Qabūl Muḥammad</persName></p>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <p>Note on flyleaf, verso and f. 1r on geometry and trigonometry. </p>
                     <p>(Endleaf, verso) A poem attributed to Amīr Khusraw Dihlavī which uses seven
                        different puns on the word '<hi rend="italic">bisyārbār</hi>', here written as prose. </p>
                     <p>Miscellaneous marginal notes apparently by the author/scribe himself. </p>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
